rules, and now they're hoping
Brexit will

30:51.717 --> 30:57.322 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
help them revitalize a fishing
industry they
say was damaged by E.U. policy.

30:57.355 --> 31:01.626 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From Southwest England, special
correspondent
Jennifer Glasse reports.

31:01.660 --> 31:04.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: Fishermen have
brought their
catches into

31:04.329 --> 31:08.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brixham Harbor since the Middle
Ages, when
it was the biggest fishing port
in Southwest

31:08.900 --> 31:11.069 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
England.

31:11.103 --> 31:13.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The harbor and the fleet have
changed over
the centuries.

31:13.972 --> 31:18.410 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And skipper Mike Sharp hopes
there are more
changes to come.

31:18.443 --> 31:20.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's why he voted for the U.K.
to leave
Europe.

31:20.612 --> 31:25.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE SHARP, Fisherman: We have
all the Dutch,
and the French, and the Belgian
fishermen,

31:25.217 --> 31:29.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and mainly the Spanish as well
coming to land
to take our fish out of our
waters, which

31:29.554 --> 31:34.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we want to -- you know, I think
we still can
let them come in, but we can
decide how many

31:34.159 --> 31:35.927 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
comes in.

31:35.961 --> 31:43.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: European
Union-mandated quotas
stipulate what kind and how many
fish the

31:43.335 --> 31:45.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
trawlers can bring in.

31:45.203 --> 31:49.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sharp and other fishermen here
claim the quotas
favor boats from continental
Europe.

31:49.808 --> 31:52.944 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
E.U. rules also limited the size
of fishing
fleets.

31:52.978 --> 31:57.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE SHARP: When I started
fishing 30 years
ago, there was 60 beam trawlers,
and now there's

31:57.449 --> 31:58.416 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
