modernized in part
with E.U. funds.

32:26.912 --> 32:30.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL MORTIMER, Brixham: A lot of
the fish
we sell in England, we sell from
this market

32:30.482 --> 32:32.250 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
here actually goes abroad.

32:32.284 --> 32:34.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think just, because we're out
of the E.U.,
I don't think they're going to
stop buying

32:34.753 --> 32:35.720 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our fish.

32:35.754 --> 32:37.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're still going to want our
fish.

32:37.656 --> 32:41.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: Fish buyer
Steve Farrar says
his children voted to stay in
Europe because

32:41.226 --> 32:43.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they want to be able to study
and work there.

32:43.395 --> 32:45.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVE FARRAR, Fish Buyer: Oh, I
don't want
them that badly.

32:45.897 --> 32:50.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: He voted to
leave because
he says it was a question of
democracy vs.

32:50.602 --> 32:52.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
control from Europe.

32:52.470 --> 32:57.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE FARRAR: I felt very much
that if I couldn't
vote somebody, a politician, in
or out, I

32:57.409 --> 33:01.379 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
