the right
kind of jobs since the local
economy has evolved.

36:59.751 --> 37:03.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONOVAN GARDNER, Food Bank
Founder: Those
jobs are not here anymore.

37:03.688 --> 37:05.657 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that -- and they're still
not here.

37:05.690 --> 37:11.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Whether it's European money or
British government
money, those cyber-jobs are not
here in Cornwall.

37:11.896 --> 37:13.665 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what we struggle
with.

37:13.698 --> 37:17.402 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JENNIFER GLASSE: Some in
Cornwall want the
government to bring back heavy
industry, not

37:17.435 --> 37:19.304 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a viable prospect.

37:19.337 --> 37:24.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And European funds have been
spent to create
21st century solutions to
Cornwall's limitations.

37:24.075 --> 37:32.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN POLLARD: A lot of that
money is not visible,
so it doesn't build a school or
a sports center.

37:32.050 --> 37:38.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It builds a road, or it builds a
business
park, or it helps to develop a
digital industry.

37:38.556 --> 37:42.193 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And people, the man in the
street doesn't
-- they don't see that.

37:42.227 --> 37:45.797 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JENNIFER GLASSE: Back in
Brixham, the fishermen
head out to sea.

37:45.830 --> 37:50.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say they have done their
part, persuading
the country to vote to get out
of Europe.

37:50.168 --> 37:52.704 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
